<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="117" type="voucher specimen">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Voucher specimen.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
Italy. Abruzzo. Salendo a Cima delle Murelle in loc. La Carozza (Pennapiedimonte, Chieti) (WGS84: 
<geoCoordinate degrees="42.11324" direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="1" value="42.11324">42.11324N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="14.14273" direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="1" value="14.14273">14.14273E</geoCoordinate>
), rupi e pendii rupestri, 2300 m, 2 August 2011, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">F. Bartolucci &amp; F. Conti</emphasis>
(APP n°59214).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="117" type="method">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Method.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Squash preparations were made on root tips obtained from cultivated plants. Root tips were pre-treated with 0.4% colchicine for 4 h and then fixed in Carnoy solution for 1 h. After hydrolysis in 1N HCl at 60 °C, the tips were stained with leuco-basic fuchsine.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="117" type="observations">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Observations.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa ligulata" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ligulata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Poa ligulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in the Iberian Peninsula and NW Africa (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.103.26029" author="Ortega-Olivencia, A" journalOrPublisher="PhytoKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="27 - 60" refId="B9" refString="Ortega-Olivencia, A, Devesa, JA, 2018. Updated checklist of Poa in the Iberian Peninsula and Balearic Islands. PhytoKeys 103: 27 - 60" title="Updated checklist of Poa in the Iberian Peninsula and Balearic Islands." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.103.26029" volume="103" year="2018">Ortega-Olivencia and Devesa 2018</bibRefCitation>
). It was not recorded for the Italian flora until recently (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/11263504.2017.1419996" author="Bartolucci, F" journalOrPublisher="Plant Biosystems" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="179 - 303" refId="B1" refString="Bartolucci, F, Peruzzi, L, Galasso, G, Albano, A, Alessandrini, A, Ardenghi, NMG, Astuti, G, Bacchetta, G, Ballelli, S, Banfi, E, Barberis, G, Bernardo, L, Bouvet, D, Bovio, M, Cecchi, L, Di Pietro, R, Domina, G, Fascetti, S, Fenu, G, Festi, F, Foggi, B, Gallo, L, Gottschlich, G, Gubellini, L, Iamonico, D, Iberite, M, Jimenez-Mejias, P, Lattanzi, E, Marchetti, D, Martinetto, E, Masin, RR, Medagli, P, Passalacqua, NG, Peccenini, S, Pennesi, R, Pierini, B, Poldini, L, Prosser, F, Raimondo, FM, Roma-Marzio, F, Rosati, L, Santangelo, A, Scoppola, A, Scortegagna, S, Selvaggi, A, Selvi, F, Soldano, A, Stinca, A, Wagensommer, RP, Wilhalm, T, Conti, F, 2018. An updated checklist of the vascular flora native to Italy. Plant Biosystems 152: 179 - 303" title="An updated checklist of the vascular flora native to Italy." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/11263504.2017.1419996" volume="152" year="2018">Bartolucci et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.412.1.1" author="Conti, F" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="1 - 90" refId="B5" refString="Conti, F, Ciaschetti, G, Di Martino, L, Bartolucci, F, 2019. An annotated checklist of the vascular flora of Majella National Park (Central Italy). Phytotaxa 412: 1 - 90" title="An annotated checklist of the vascular flora of Majella National Park (Central Italy)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.412.1.1" volume="412" year="2019">Conti et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
). This is the first chromosome count for this species in Italy (
<bibRefCitation author="Bedini, G" journalOrPublisher="Plant Biosystems" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" publicationUrl="http://bot.biologia.unipi.it/chrobase/" refId="B2" refString="Bedini, G, Garbari, F, Peruzzi, L, 2010. .http://bot.biologia.unipi.it/chrobase/" url="http://bot.biologia.unipi.it/chrobase/" year="2010">Bedini et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
onwards), and it agrees with previous chromosome numbers published from Spain (
<bibRefCitation author="Kuepfer, P" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe Neuchateloise des Sciences Naturelles" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="87 - 104" refId="B7" refString="Kuepfer, P, 1968. Nouvelles prospections caryologiques dans le flore orophile des Pyrenees et de la Sierra Nevada. Bulletin de la Societe Neuchateloise des Sciences Naturelles 91: 87 - 104" title="Nouvelles prospections caryologiques dans le flore orophile des Pyrenees et de la Sierra Nevada." volume="91" year="1968">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Küpfer">Kuepfer</normalizedToken>
1968
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Loeve, A" journalOrPublisher="Lagascalia" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="147 - 182" refId="B8" refString="Loeve, A, Kjellqvist, E, 1973. Cytotaxonomy of Spanish plants. II. Monocotyledons. Lagascalia 3: 147 - 182" title="Cytotaxonomy of Spanish plants. II. Monocotyledons." volume="3" year="1973">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Löve">Loeve</normalizedToken>
and Kjellqvist 1973
</bibRefCitation>
). On the basis of a preliminary morphological analysis, the population from central Italy shows peculiar features, and a taxonomic study is in progress.
</paragraph>
